DEFINITIONS

"Non-Production Use" means use of the Licensed Work for development,
testing, staging, prototyping, demonstration, or other activities that
do not serve end users or systems in a live production environment. For
the avoidance of doubt, Non-Production Use does not include deployment
to any environment that handles live customer traffic, processes real
customer data, or provides functionality to end users.

"Non-Commercial Purpose" means personal use, evaluation, testing,
demonstration, or research where the primary intent is not to generate
revenue, commercial advantage, or monetary compensation. Use by a
for-profit entity for internal tooling, prototyping, or evaluation that
does not directly serve paying customers or directly generate revenue
qualifies as Non-Commercial Purpose. Use by a not-for-profit
organization in furtherance of its charitable mission also qualifies as
Non-Commercial Purpose.

"Academic Purpose" means use by students, faculty, staff, or researchers
at a degree-granting educational institution (including university-
affiliated hospitals, laboratories, and research institutes), or by
independent researchers affiliated with a recognized non-profit research
organization, for the purposes of teaching, scholarly research, or
publication, provided that any resulting products or services are not
offered commercially.

